Saint Peter's, Wofford, Gonzaga, Old Dominion Book NCAA Tournament Berths

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-03-08T05:21:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/saint-peter-s-wofford-gonzaga-old-dominion-book-ncaa-tournament-berths.html
Saint Peter’s College is headed to
the national men’s basketball tournament for the first time
since 1995 after beating Iona College 62-57 in the title game of
the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference tournament.  Jason Belin scored 17 points yesterday to lead  Jersey City ,
New Jersey-based  Saint Peter’s  (20-13), which avenged a pair of
double-digit regular-season losses against Iona.  Saint Peter’s ended Iona’s nine-game winning streak to
claim the MAAC’s automatic berth in the National Collegiate
Athletic Association tournament. It will be the third NCAA
appearance for the Peacocks, who also beat Loyola of  Maryland 
and top-seeded Fairfield en route to the MAAC title.  “It wasn’t the prettiest three games, but at the end of
the day we had enough mental toughness to get it done,” Saint
Peter’s coach John Dunne said in a televised interview.  Wofford College  is headed to the NCAA tournament for the
second year in a row after beating the College of Charleston 77-
67 to win the Southern Conference title. Cameron Rundles scored
21 points to lead Spartanburg, South Carolina-based Wofford,
which improved to 21-12.  Old Dominion University  and Gonzaga University also
clinched automatic NCAA berths by winning their conference
tournaments yesterday. Norfolk, Virginia-based Old Dominion (27-
6) beat Virginia Commonwealth 70-65 for the Colonial Athletic
Association title, while Spokane, Washington-based Gonzaga (24-
9) won an 11th West Coast Conference crown with a 75-63 victory
over St. Mary’s of  California .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
